<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="29" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1451,1763,2042]" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,335,1763,1789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Distribution</emphasis>
:—Endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[510,588,1763,1789]" name="Gabon" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Gabon</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[601,928,1763,1789]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Bulbophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pauwelsianum">
<emphasis box="[601,928,1763,1789]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Bulbophyllum pauwelsianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in Atlantic Central Africa (
<figureCitation box="[1325,1394,1763,1790]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1695,1717]" captionTargetBox="[184,1429,686,1637]" captionTargetId="figure-300@3.[151,1435,674,1667]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution of Bulbophyllum pauwelsianum in Gabon (Central Africa)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5153697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5153697/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) and has been recorded to date from only the Ndjolé and the Kinguélé areas, both sites situated in the mountainous area of the Monts de Cristal. The distribution of this species corresponds to the Atlantic Sector of the Lower 
<collectingCountry box="[1273,1354,1835,1861]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Guinea</collectingCountry>
Domain (
<bibRefCitation author="Senterre, B." box="[144,309,1871,1898]" pageId="3" pageNumber="29" pagination="409 - 419" refId="ref5330" refString="Senterre, B. (2005) Methodological research for the typology of the vegetation and phytogeography of denses African tropical forests. Acta Botanica Gallica 152 (3): 409 - 419." type="journal article" year="2005">Senterre 2005</bibRefCitation>
), which is the coastal part of the Lower 
<collectingCountry box="[791,872,1871,1897]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Guinea</collectingCountry>
Domain of the Guineo-Congolian Region (
<bibRefCitation author="White, F." pageId="3" pageNumber="29" pagination="11 - 55" refId="ref5963" refString="White, F. (1979) The Guineo-Congolian Region and its relationships to other phytochoria. Bulletin du Jardin botanique national de Belgique 49: 11 - 55. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 3667815" type="journal article" year="1979">White 1979</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1451,1763,2042]" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,437,1943,1970]" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Habitat and Ecology</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName box="[473,800,1943,1969]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Bulbophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pauwelsianum">
<emphasis box="[473,800,1943,1969]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Bulbophyllum pauwelsianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found in very humid forest. The elevation range of the species was estimated to be around 
<specimenCount box="[536,614,1980,2006]" pageId="3" pageNumber="29" type="generic">
<quantity box="[536,610,1980,2006]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="29" unit="m" value="200.0">200 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1451,1763,2042]" box="[189,625,2015,2042]" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,313,2016,2042]" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Phenology</emphasis>
:—Flowering in November.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
